title: Kyiv says it killed Russian admiral. Moscow says he’s taking video calls.
description: Ukraine claims that a strike on Crimea killed Russian Admiral Viktor Sokolov. Russia claims that he is alive and on video.

title: Trump administration officials ordered to testify on family separations
description: A magistrate judge ordered federal officials and lawyers for migrants to schedule depositions of two former Trump administration officials on family separations

title: Canada’s House speaker steps down after honoring Nazi veteran
description: The speaker, Anthony Rota, said on Tuesday that he would step down after honoring a member of a Waffen-SS unit in Parliament.

title: U.S. demands protection for civilians as thousands leave Nagorno-Karabakh
description: Mass evacuations were underway as Azerbaijan pushed to reassert full control over the disputed region, and the largely ethnic Armenian population fled.

title: Humans of Bombay is suing another spinoff. Humans of New York isn’t happy.
description: Humans of New York creator Brandon Stanton said Humans of Bombay, a similar platform started by Karishma Mehta, has appropriated his work.

title: Monster machines floating on the waves could be the future of wind energy
description: These next-generation machines can be deployed in deep water, where they can harvest stronger, more consistent wind.

title: Police militias used to fight Brazil’s gangs. Now they extort, traffic and kill, too.
description: Bands of active-duty and retired police, once accepted as semi-official adjuncts to law enforcement, threaten the nation’s democracy.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky confirms arrival of first U.S.-made M1 Abrams tanks
description: U.S. military officials have said that the deliveries would be gradual but that they expected all 31 of them to arrive in coming weeks.

title: An Armenian exodus raises the specter of ‘ethnic cleansing’
description: An entire community may be on the verge of abandoning its ancestral homeland.
